objectives.name: Primary Objective
objectives.text: To determine the benefit of enzalutamide plus ADT as compared to placebo plus ADT as assessed by radiographic progression-free survival (rPFS) based on central review

objectives.name: Secondary Objective - OS
objectives.text: To determine the benefit of enzalutamide plus ADT as compared to placebo plus ADT as assessed by overall survival (OS)

objectives.name: Secondary Objective - SSE
objectives.text: To determine the benefit of enzalutamide plus ADT as compared to placebo plus ADT as assessed by time to first Symptomatic Skeletal Event (SSE)

objectives.name: Secondary Objective - Castration Resistance
objectives.text: To determine the benefit of enzalutamide plus ADT as compared to placebo plus ADT as assessed by time to castration resistance

objectives.name: Secondary Objective - QoL
objectives.text: To determine the benefit of enzalutamide plus ADT as compared to placebo plus ADT as assessed by Quality of Life (QoL) (as measured by Quality of Life Prostate-specific Questionnaire [QLQ-PR25] / Functional Assessment of Cancer Therapy-Prostate [FACT-P] and EuroQol Group-5 Dimension-5 Level Instrument [EQ-5D-5L])

objectives.name: Secondary Objective - Antineoplastic Therapy
objectives.text: To determine the benefit of enzalutamide plus ADT as compared to placebo plus ADT as assessed by time to start of new antineoplastic therapy

objectives.name: Secondary Objective - PSA Progression
objectives.text: To determine the benefit of enzalutamide plus ADT as compared to placebo plus ADT as assessed by time to prostate-specific antigen (PSA) progression

objectives.name: Secondary Objective - PSA Undetectable
objectives.text: To determine the benefit of enzalutamide plus ADT as compared to placebo plus ADT as assessed by PSA undetectable rate (< 0.2 ng/mL)

objectives.name: Secondary Objective - ORR
objectives.text: To determine the benefit of enzalutamide plus ADT as compared to placebo plus ADT as assessed by objective response rate (ORR)

objectives.name: Secondary Objective - Pain
objectives.text: To determine the benefit of enzalutamide plus ADT as compared to placebo plus ADT as assessed by worsening of pain (as measured by Brief Pain Inventory-Short Form [BPI-SF])

objectives.name: Safety Objective
objectives.text: To determine the safety of enzalutamide plus ADT as compared to placebo plus ADT

objectives.name: Exploratory Objective
objectives.text: To determine gene mutations potentially related to resistance of enzalutamide plus ADT as assessed by DNA mutation testing in plasma

endpoints.name: Time to deterioration in urinary symptoms
endpoints.text: Time to deterioration in urinary symptoms

endpoints.name: Time to initiation of new antineoplastic therapy
endpoints.text: Time to initiation of new antineoplastic therapy

endpoints.name: Time to PSA progression
endpoints.text: Time to PSA progression (≥ 2 ng/mL) (Prostate Cancer Clinical Trials Working Group 2 criteria)

endpoints.name: Adverse Events
endpoints.text: Nature, frequency and severity of adverse events

endpoints.name: Safety laboratory tests
endpoints.text: Safety laboratory tests: biochemistry and hematology

endpoints.name: Vital signs
endpoints.text: Vital signs (blood pressure, pulse and temperature)

endpoints.name: Mutation status
endpoints.text: Mutation status in plasma of genes potentially related to resistance of enzalutamide plus ADT

estimands.name: Primary Efficacy Estimand - rPFS
estimands.populationSummary: Adult patients with metastatic hormone sensitive prostate cancer (mHSPC) (ITT population) Summary measure: Hazard ratio from stratified Cox Regression.

intercurrentEvents.name: Death
intercurrentEvents.text: Death from any cause within 24 weeks after study drug discontinuation

intercurrentEvents.name: Treatment discontinuation without progression
intercurrentEvents.text: Subject discontinues study treatment for reasons other than radiographic progression

intercurrentEvents.name: Initiation of new antineoplastic therapy
intercurrentEvents.text: Starting an investigational agent or new therapy for treatment of prostate cancer prior to radiographic progression

estimands.analysisPopulation: Adult patients with metastatic hormone sensitive prostate cancer (mHSPC) (ITT population)

estimands.summaryMeasure: Hazard ratio from stratified Cox Regression

estimands.name: Secondary Efficacy Estimand - OS

intercurrentEvents.name: Treatment switching/crossover
intercurrentEvents.text: Placebo subjects receiving enzalutamide after progression or study unblinding

estimands.treatment: Enzalutamide 160 mg daily plus ADT vs Placebo plus ADT
estimands.analysisPopulation: Adult patients with metastatic hormone sensitive prostate cancer (mHSPC) (ITT population)
estimands.summaryMeasure: Hazard ratio from stratified Cox Regression

estimands.name: Secondary Efficacy Estimand - PSA Undetectable Rate
estimands.populationSummary: Adult patients with mHSPC and detectable PSA (≥ 0.2 ng/mL) at baseline Summary measure: Odds ratio using stratified Cochran-Mantel-Haenszel score test.

intercurrentEvents.name: Treatment discontinuation
intercurrentEvents.text: Discontinuation of study drug prior to achieving undetectable PSA

estimands.analysisPopulation: Adult patients with mHSPC and detectable PSA (≥ 0.2 ng/mL) at baseline
estimands.summaryMeasure: Odds ratio using stratified Cochran-Mantel-Haenszel score test
